{"title":"Unlevered Beta and CAPM (Using Business Risk Only)","markdown":{"headingText":"Unlevered Beta and CAPM (Using Business Risk Only)","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n```{r}\n#| eval: true\n#| results: asis\n#| echo: false\n#| warning: false\nlibrary(webexercises)\n\n# Randomized parameters\nset.seed(303)\nbeta_L <- round(rnorm(1, mean = 1.50, sd = 0.20), 2)        # levered beta\nD_over_E <- round(runif(1, min = 0.30, max = 0.80), 2)      # debt-to-equity\ntax <- round(runif(1, min = 0.20, max = 0.35), 2)           # corporate tax rate\nrf <- round(runif(1, min = 0.02, max = 0.05), 2)            # risk-free (decimal)\nrm <- round(runif(1, min = 0.08, max = 0.12), 2)            # market return (decimal)\n\nbeta_U <- beta_L / (1 + (1 - tax) * D_over_E)               # unlevered (asset) beta\nRe_unlev <- rf + beta_U * (rm - rf)                         # CAPM with unlevered beta\n\nbeta_U_disp <- round(beta_U, 2)\nRe_unlev_pct <- round(100*Re_unlev, 2)\n```\n\nA firm has **levered beta = `r beta_L`**, **D/E = `r D_over_E`**, **tax rate = `r round(100*tax,2)`**%.  \nWhat is its **unlevered (asset) beta**? (Use the standard formula removing leverage.)\n\n::: {.question-block}\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module4_num_q1a\"><strong>1. Unlevered beta (no units):</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module4_num_q1a\" name=\"module4_num_q1a\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 160px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=`r beta_U_disp` data-tolerance=\"0.1\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module4_num_q1a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n✅ **Why this is the answer:** Unlevered beta measures **business risk only** (no financial leverage).  \nWe “strip out” leverage using: β<sub>U</sub> = β<sub>L</sub> / [1 + (1 – T) × (D/E)].  \nThis lets us compare firms **on operating risk**, independent of capital structure.  \n**Your numbers:** β<sub>U</sub> = `r beta_L` / [1 + (1 − `r tax`) × `r D_over_E`] = **`r beta_U_disp`**.\n</div>\n:::\n\nIf the **risk-free rate** is **`r round(100*rf,2)`**% and the **expected market return** is **`r round(100*rm,2)`**%, what is the **expected return using CAPM with the unlevered beta**?\n\n::: {.question-block}\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module4_num_q1b\"><strong>2. Expected return (in %):</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module4_num_q1b\" name=\"module4_num_q1b\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 160px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=`r Re_unlev_pct` data-tolerance=\"0.1\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module4_num_q1b\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n✅ **CAPM intuition:** Investors require compensation for time value (**Rf**) and for bearing market risk (**β × MRP**).  \nWe use the **unlevered beta** to price the **business risk** without leverage:  \nE[R] = R<sub>f</sub> + β<sub>U</sub> × (R<sub>m</sub> − R<sub>f</sub>) = **`r Re_unlev_pct`%**.  \nThis gives a **baseline cost of equity** for the project/asset **before** financing effects.\n</div>\n:::\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"knitr"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"scroll",